        <indexterm>verb<indexterm><keyword
              conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/vbnmtrv"/> (<keyword
              conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/vbcltrv"/>)</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <refbody>
    <section>
      <p>This verb generates and verifies transaction values based on information from the
        transaction and a cryptographic key. You select the validation method, and either the
        generate or verify mode, through <i>rule_array</i> keywords.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <p>For the <keyword conref="wskc_conref-l0wskc04.dita#conref-l0wskc04/amex"/> process, the
        control vector supplied with the cryptographic key must indicate a MAC or MACVER class key.
        The key can be single or double length. <synph><kwd>DATAM</kwd></synph> and
            <synph><kwd>DATAMV</kwd></synph> keys are not supported. The MAC generate control vector
        bit must be on (bit 20) if you request CSC generation and MAC verify bit (bit 21) must be on
        if you request verification.</p>
    </section>
  </refbody>
